  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a horizontal portion of a circuit that has a resistor, a voltmeter, and an ammeter. From left to right, along the horizontal branch portion is a point labeled X, followed by the resistor, followed by the ammeter, followed by a point labeled Y. An additional subbranch is indicated that connects point X to point Y, and it has the voltmeter.\" height=\"108\" src=\"/images/9ab89c9bca32fe4f51d36abe6876478a.svg\" width=\"274\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The circuit elements shown in the diagram is part of a larger circuit containing a battery and other resistors. A potential difference of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2.0 volts\"><math alttext=\"2.0 volts\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2.0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>V</mtext></math></span></span> is measured with the voltmeter, and a current of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.20 amp\"><math alttext=\"0.20 amp\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.20</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> is measured with the ammeter. Which of the following changes would result in a current of zero between points <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
